http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Panchayat-poll-process-begins/article14020390.ece

The procedure of conduct of elections to the 90-member Belagavi Zilla Panchayat and 345 seats of taluk panchayats in the district commenced with the issue of notification by the District Returning Officer and Deputy Commissioner N. Jayaram on Monday.The last date of filing nominations is February 1 and the last date for withdrawal of nominations is February 4. Polling will be held on February 13 and counting of ballot papers at taluk centres on February 23.Of the 90 seats in Belagavi Zilla Panchayat, 45 is reserved for women, which includes six seats for Scheduled Castes, seven for Scheduled Tribes, eleven for Backward Class-A and three for BC-B. Of the 345 seats under ten taluk panchayats, 176 has been reserved for women, including 82 belonging to general category. 2,940 polling stations will be set up and the cost involved for conducting elections in one polling station would be approximately Rs.18,000.